<namespaces>
  <namespace name="Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web">
    For the list of available business object controls see the 
    <see href="Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web.Controls.html">Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web.Controls</see> namespace.
  </namespace>
  <namespace name="Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web.Controls">
    The <c>Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web.Controls</c> namespace provides object bindable controls implementing 
    <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web.Controls.IBusinessObjectBoundWebControl"/>. If the control provides edit 
    functionality, it also implements <see cref="T:Rubicon.Web.UI.ISmartControl"/>. When used together with a 
    <see cref="T:Rubicon.Web.UI.Controls.FormGridManager"/>, the bound web controls provide a maximum of usability 
    with a minimum of coding effort.
  <h3 class="dtH3">Business Object Bound Controls</h3>
  <table class="dtTABLE" style="width: 94%" cellspacing="0">
    <thead>
      <tr valign="top">
        <th width="25%">Type</th>
        <th width="75%">Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web.Controls.BocBooleanValue"/></td>
        <td>
           Use this control for displaying and editing the value of an 
          <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObjectBooleanProperty"/>, 
          a <see cref="T:System.Boolean"/> or <see cref="T:Rubicon.NullableValueTypes.NaBoolean"/> value and 
          <see langword="null"/>.
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web.Controls.BocDateTimeValue"/></td>
        <td>
           Use this control for displaying and editing the value of an 
          <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObjectDateProperty"/>, 
          <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObjectDateTimeProperty"/>, a <see cref="T:System.DateTime"/>
          or <see cref="T:Rubicon.NullableValueTypes.NaDateTime"/> value and <see langword="null"/>.
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web.Controls.BocEnumValue"/></td>
        <td>
           Use this control for displaying and editing the value of an 
          <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObjectEnumerationProperty"/>, 
          an <see cref="T:System.Enum"/> value and <see langword="null"/>.
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web.Controls.BocList"/></td>
        <td>
          <para>
             Use this control for displaying the value of an <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObjectReferenceProperty"/> 
            having <see cref="P:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObjectProperty.IsList"/> set <see langword="true"/> 
            or an <see cref="T:System.Collections.IList"/> of <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObject"/> 
            objects and <see langword="null"/>.
          </para><para>
            The <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web.Controls.BocList"/> supports editing the the values the 
            individual rows, attatching hyperlinks, events, or an 
            <see cref="T:Rubicon.Web.ExecutionEngine.WxeFunction"/> to the cells or the entire list.
          </para> 
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web.Controls.BocMultilineTextValue"/></td>
        <td>
           Use this control for displaying and editing the value of an 
          <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObjectStringProperty"/> 
          having <see cref="P:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObjectProperty.IsList"/> set <see langword="true"/> 
          or a <see cref="T:System.String"/> array and <see langword="null"/>.
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web.Controls.BocReferenceValue"/></td>
        <td>
          <para>
             Use this control for displaying and editing the value of an 
            <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObjectReferenceProperty"/> 
            populated with an <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObjectWithIdentity"/>, 
            or <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObjectWithIdentity"/> and <see langword="null"/> if used 
            without data binding.
          </para><para>
            The <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web.Controls.BocReferenceValue"/> supports attatching hyperlinks, 
            events, or an <see cref="T:Rubicon.Web.ExecutionEngine.WxeFunction"/> to the currently selected value
            or the control itself.
          </para> 
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web.Controls.BocTextValue"/></td>
        <td>
           Use this control for displaying and editing the value of an 
          <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObjectStringProperty"/>,
          an <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObjectNumericProperty"/>, 
          an <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObjectDateProperty"/>,
          or an <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObjectDateTimeProperty"/> when used with data binding.
          It can also be assigned a <see cref="T:System.String"/>, an <see cref="T:System.Int32"/>, 
          a <see cref="T:System.Double"/>, or a <see cref="T:System.DateTime"/> and <see langword="null"/>.
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web.Controls.BocTreeView"/></td>
        <td>
          Use this control for displaying a hierarchy of <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObjectWithIdentity"/> 
          and <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObjectReferenceProperty"/> objects.
        </td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <h3 class="dtH3">Business Object Data Source Controls</h3>
  <table class="dtTABLE" style="width: 94%" cellspacing="0">
    <thead>
      <tr valign="top">
        <th width="25%">Type</th>
        <th width="75%">Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web.Controls.IBusinessObjectDataSourceControl"/></td>
        <td>
          <para>
            Use this control for binding an <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObject"/> 
            to an <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web.Controls.IBusinessObjectBoundWebControl"/> on your page.
          </para><para>
            Each business object implementation, consisting of implementations for 
            <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObject"/>, 
            <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObjectProperty"/> and 
            <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObjectClass"/> must also provide a matching implementation of
            <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web.Controls.IBusinessObjectDataSourceControl"/>. The abstract class 
            <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web.Controls.BusinessObjectDataSourceControl"/> provides a default 
            implementation from which to inherit from.
          </para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web.Controls.BusinessObjectReferenceDataSourceControl"/></td>
        <td>
          Use this control for cascading business objects on a web page, i.e. displaying or editing the property value
          of an <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObject"/> pointed to by the primary business object's
          <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObjectReferenceProperty"/>.
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web.Controls.BusinessObjectReferenceSearchDataSourceControl"/></td>
        <td>
          Use this control to provide an otherwise unbound <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web.Controls.BocList"/> 
          with an <see cref="T:Rubicon.ObjectBinding.IBusinessObjectClass"/>.
        </td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  </namespace>
</namespaces>